e) <BR> conj <BR> 2) because that, because, notwithstanding, although"}}, {:source=>{:book=>"genesis", :chapter=>8, :verse=>11, :reference=>"genesis 8:11", :text=>"the earth"}, :hebrew=>{:word=>"׃ץֶרָֽאָה", :translit=>"hā-’ā-reṣ.", :defined=>"ha·'A·retz.: the earth ", :stats=>[{:occurance=>"45", :total=>"934"}]}, :strongs=>{:strong_number=>"776", :strong_definition=>"Strong's Hebrew 776: 1) land, earth<BR> 1a) earth <BR> 1a1) whole earth (as opposed to a part) <BR> 1a2) earth (as opposed to heaven) <BR> 1a3) earth (inhabitants) <BR> 1b) land <BR> 1b1) country, territory <BR> 1b2) district, region <BR> 1b3) tribal territory <BR> 1b4) piece of ground <BR> 1b5) land of Canaan, Israel <BR> 1b6) inhabitants of land <BR> 1b7) Sheol, land without return, (under) world <BR> 1b8) city (-state) <BR> 1c) ground, surface of the earth <BR> 1c1) ground <BR> 1c2) soil <BR> 1d) (in phrases) <BR> 1d1) people of the land <BR> 1d2) space or distance of country (in measurements of distance) <BR> 1d3) level or plain country <BR> 1d4) land of the living <BR> 1d5) end(s) of the earth <BR> 1e) (almost wholly late in usage) <BR> 1e1) lands, countries <BR> 1e1a) often in contrast to Canaan"}}], :versions=>[{:version=>"New International Version", :text=>"When the dove returned to him in the evening, there in its beak was a freshly plucked olive leaf! Then Noah knew that the water had receded from the earth."}, {:version=>"New Living Translation", :text=>"This time the dove returned to him in the evening with a fresh olive leaf in its beak. Then Noah knew that the floodwaters were almost gone."}, {:version=>"English Standard Version", :text=>"And the dove came back to him in the evening, and behold, in her mouth was a freshly plucked olive leaf. So Noah knew that the waters had subsided from the earth."}, {:version=>"Berean Study Bible", :text=>"And behold, the dove returned to him in the evening with a freshly plucked olive leaf in her beak. So Noah knew that the waters had receded from the earth."}, {:version=>"New American Standard Bible ", :text=>"The dove came to him toward evening, and behold, in her beak was a freshly picked olive leaf. So Noah knew that the water was abated from the earth."}, {:version=>"New King James Version", :text=>"Then the dove came to him in the evening, and behold, a freshly plucked olive leaf "}, {:version=>" in her mouth; and Noah knew that the waters had receded from the earth.", :text=>"King James Bible"}, {:version=>"And the dove came in to him in the evening; and, lo, in her mouth ", :text=>" an olive leaf pluckt off: so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth."}, {:version=>"Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"When the dove came to him at evening, there was a plucked olive leaf in its beak. So Noah knew that the water on the earth's surface had gone down."}, {:version=>"Contemporary English Version", :text=>"It returned in the evening, holding in its beak a green leaf from an olive tree. Noah knew the water was finally going down. "}, {:version=>"Good News Translation", :text=>"It returned to him in the evening with a fresh olive leaf in its beak. So Noah knew that the water had gone down. "}, {:version=>"Holman Christian Standard Bible", :text=>"When the dove came to him at evening, there was a plucked olive leaf in her beak. So Noah knew that the water on the earth's surface had gone down. "}, {:version=>"International Standard Version", :text=>"The dove returned to him in the evening, but in its beak there was an olive leaf that it had plucked! So Noah knew that the flood waters had decreased on the land. "}, {:version=>"NET Bible", :text=>"When the dove returned to him in the evening, there was a freshly plucked olive leaf in its beak! Noah knew that the waters had receded from the earth."}, {:version=>"New Heart English Bible", :text=>"The dove came back to him at evening, and, look, in her mouth was an olive leaf plucked off. So Noah knew that the waters had abated from the earth."}, {:version=>"GOD'S WORD® Translation", :text=>"The dove came to him in the evening, and in its beak was a freshly plucked olive leaf. Then Noah knew that the water was gone from the earth."}, {:version=>"JPS Tanakh 1917", :text=>"And the dove came in to him at eventide; and lo in her mouth an olive-leaf freshly plucked; so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth."}, {:version=>"New American Standard 1977 ", :text=>"And the dove came to him toward evening; and behold, in her beak was a freshly picked olive leaf. So Noah knew that the water was abated from the earth."}, {:version=>"King James 2000 Bible", :text=>"And the dove came in to him in the evening; and, lo, in her mouth was a plucked off olive leaf: so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth."}, {:version=>"American King James Version", :text=>"And the dove came in to him in the evening; and, see, in her mouth was an olive leaf plucked off: so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth."}, {:version=>"American Standard Version", :text=>"and the dove came in to him at eventide; and, lo, in her mouth an olive-leaf plucked off: so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth."}, {:version=>"Brenton Septuagint Translation", :text=>"And the dove returned to him in the evening, and had a leaf of olive, a sprig in her mouth; and Noe knew that the water had ceased from off the earth."}, {:version=>"Douay-Rheims Bible", :text=>"And she came to him in the evening, carrying a bough of an olive tree, with green leaves, in her mouth. Noe therefore understood that the waters were ceased upon the earth. "}, {:version=>"Darby Bible Translation", :text=>"And the dove came to him at eventide; and behold, in her beak was an olive-leaf plucked off; and Noah knew that the waters had become low on the earth."}, {:version=>"English Revised Version", :text=>"and the dove came in to him at eventide; and, lo, in her mouth an olive leaf pluckt off: so Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth."}, {:version=>"Webster's Bible Translation", :text=>"And the dove came in to him in the evening, and lo, in her mouth was an olive-leaf plucked off: So Noah knew that the waters were abated from off the earth."}, {:version=>"World English Bible", :text=>"The dove came back to him at evening, and, behold, in her mouth was an olive leaf plucked off. So Noah knew that the waters were abated from the earth."}, {:version=>"Young's Literal Translation", :text=>" and the dove cometh in unto him at even-time, and lo, an olive leaf torn off in her mouth; and Noah knoweth that the waters have been lightened from off the earth."}]}